me in beta up to level 22.....<br>
<br>
1-4: Any newbie area. I used Prendwyn(sp?) Keep mostly.<br>
<br>
5-8: Bandit area North of the bridge to West Downs.<br>
<br>
9-14: Salisbury Plains along the road opposite West Downs. Also in the Northern half of Campo Forest.<br>
<br>
15 - 18: Avalon Marsh, across the bridge from Adribard's Retreat on the Cornwall side of the river. Ghouls are excellent experience and loot for this level range in a full group.<br>
<br>
19 - 22: Cornwall. Start with undead Romans, then cliff spiders moving up to Cornish Hunters, elder beeches and finally (at about level 22 at the earliest) rooters at the hog farm.<br>
<br>
Other good spots I found, but can't remember at what levels I hunted there: Snowdonia, Llyn Barfog (this was in the late teens and the area was too difficult for us at that level), Suavage Forest (RvR area, so heads up, but also good hunting in the early 20's). I didn't use any of the dungeons for experience hunting, but they are great experience as well. From what I've seen (I hunted three dungeons in Albion) you're always better off with a full group in a dungeon.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps!<br>
<br>
Dog<br>
